      "options": {
        "code": { "language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false, "showMiniMap": false },
        "content": "### Per-user, per-node breakdown is not available\n\n3x-ui aggregates client traffic **centrally by email** (single `client_traffics` row per client, summed across all nodes). The per-inbound `clientStats` exposed by the API are replicated across the client's inbounds in multi-node setups, so a per-node / per-inbound split for a single user **cannot be computed reliably** and would double-count.\n\n- **Per-user totals** above use the authoritative email-keyed counters (`xui_client_traffic_*`).\n- For **per-node traffic**, see the *Traffic by Node* section (inbound-level `xui_inbound_*`).",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Why no per-node split here?",
      "type": "text"
    }
